Mark --

No one else on the Internet will ever find out about your MX record for
OTHER.COM, since there is no path from the root servers to you for that
domain.  People will no more think to ask you about OTHER.COM than they
would think to ask us here at UCLA.

What you need to do is have the OTHER.COM folks register their domain
with the NIC, and have MAILHOST.MYDOMAIN.COM listed as their mail for-
warder via an MX record.

The OTHER.COM folks should send their request to HOSTMASTER@NIC.DDN.MIL.

Once all is done, chances are that the NIC will simply stick the MX rec-
ord for OTHER.COM into the root servers.

Remember, the name OTHER.COM (or whatever name they really want) will
not be official until/unless it's registered with the NIC.

